Ad Text:
Mass Electronics Group (MEG) is a proudly Brisbane-based, family-owned business with over 35 years of experience designing and manufacturing cutting-edge products for environmental monitoring and control. Our integrated teams in Research and Development (R&D), Manufacturing, Sales, Project, Service & Distribution work together to turn ideas into commercial realities.

We’re more than just a company, we’re a community that values diverse thinking, collaboration, and innovation. With branches across two states and a legacy of excellence, MEG is a place where your ideas matter and your career can thrive.

As the Research & Development wing of MEG, Innotech Pty Ltd is responsible for designing new products for the HVAC marketplace, from concept to manufacture. Our products are renowned for their superior quality, ease of operation, technological excellence, and our R&D team ensures these attributes are built into every product we create. We offer real opportunities to grow your career while working on meaningful, high-impact projects.




About the role

Innotech Pty Ltd is seeking a passionate Embedded Software Engineer to become a valued member of our Research and Development team. In this full-time role, you’ll provide essential technical development, and project coordination support, reporting directly to the Chief Operations Officer. Your duties and responsibilities include, but are not limited to:

Designing and implementing embedded software applications and drivers

Supporting hardware prototyping and component testing throughout the development cycle

Maintaining embedded operating systems and managing source code repositories

Conducting research into emerging technologies and developing proof-of-concept solutions

Collaborating with internal teams and external stakeholders to gather requirements and contribute to product specifications


Benefits on offer

Competitive salary package based on the experience and skills of the successful candidate

Rostered day off every month

Modern, well-equipped workspace with excellent access to nearby public transport

Stability in a long-established business proud of their inclusive culture and working environment.  

Opportunity for career growth within a leading Australian manufacturer of BMS and HVAC control systems, known for innovation, reliability, and industry excellence.   

 

Experience and qualifications

Degree in Electronics, Mechatronics or Software Engineering

3+ years of embedded software development experience using C/C++

Strong debugging skills and ability to interpret electronic schematics

Experience with microcontrollers (e.g., STM32, AM335x), RTOS, Embedded Linux, and version control/build systems

Familiarity with scripting (BASH/Python) and using electronics test equipment such as multimeters and oscilloscopes

 

How to apply
If this role sounds like you, please click on the apply button and follow the prompts. We will get in touch if you are shortlisted for this opportunity.

About Us

Let’s create a more sociable future together

At Endeavour, we’re totally into what we do. With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, we love to bring people together. Together we share our passion for our products and industry; it’s what inspires us to dream big, and continue to create new experiences for our customers and teams across Australia. If you thrive on positive energy, we want to meet you!

About the Role

Bring your passion and feel the energy 
Hybrid ways of working
Corporate Benefits

Are you a passionate and skilled engineer ready to shape the future of observability? Endeavour Group, Australia’s largest retail drinks network and a leading hotel portfolio, is seeking an Observability Engineer to be a driving force in our Corporate Technology team in Sydney.

In this pivotal role, you'll be at the forefront of our observability strategy, leading the expansion and deep integration of Dynatrace across our diverse organization. You'll transform raw telemetry data into actionable, business-centric insights, empowering our development, operations, and product teams. This is a unique opportunity to build our observability practice on a greenfield foundation, defining standards, automating critical processes, and championing a culture of proactive, data-driven problem-solving.

Sound good? Read on.

Here is a taster of what you can expect in this role:

Observability Adoption

Drive Dynatrace Adoption: Lead the expansion of the Dynatrace platform across new business units and applications through collaboration with development teams and application owners to ascertain business objectives and ensure comprehensive visibility into our distributed systems operating across various clouds and data centers.
Build the Foundation: Collaborate with engineering teams to define and implement standards for instrumentation, logging, and tracing. You will be instrumental in establishing our first Service Level Objectives (SLOs) and error budgets.
Consultation & Education: Provide expert guidance and training to internal teams on Dynatrace best practices, empowering them to effectively utilise observability data for application performance understanding.
Run Observability enablement sessions to demo new Dynatrace features and pair on DQL to raise the organisation’s observability literacy.

Observability Instrumentation and Onboarding

Automate to Innovate: Design and implement automated problem remediation workflows using Dynatrace's capabilities to handle repetitive incidents, reduce manual toil, and improve system resilience.
Master the Data with DQL: Become the go-to expert for Dynatrace Query Language (DQL). You will build and maintain advanced dashboards, notebooks, and custom alerts that provide clear, actionable insights tailored to various stakeholders.
Observability Agent Instrumentation: Automate the deployment and configuration of observability agents across all supported platforms and infrastructure across cloud, on-premises, and hybrid environments, collaborating with product owners, DevOps, infrastructure, and cybersecurity teams, and provide comprehensive documentation for future self-sufficient deployments.
Embedding observability in the software development life cycle and ITSM processes including change management, release management and service transition. 

Incident Management and Problem Management

Proactive Anomaly Detection: Proactively identify and drive resolution of anomalies or performance degradation of key user journeys through relevant reporting, alerting and telemetry data.
Incident Response Expertise: Act as a subject matter expert during production incidents, leveraging observability data to expedite root cause analysis and minimise Mean Time to Resolution (MTTR).

Observability Maintenance & Continuous Improvement

Configure & Optimise: Continuously refine and tune the Dynatrace environment, such as Detection Rules, Davis Anomaly Detection, Integrations, OpenPipeline and Workflows to ensure we are capturing the right data (Metrics, Events, Logs and Traces) and minimising noise.
Observability Practice: Help facilitate the functions and initiatives of the Observability Centre of Excellence, including Technical Knowledge Articles, Documentation and the Observability Framework.
Observability Support Channels: Assist stakeholders with their support requests via chat channels or ServiceNOW tickets.
Maturing Observability Practice: Proactively identifies areas for improvement, focusing on streamlining processes and enhancing service quality.

What do we need from you

Now let’s talk about you: 

Significant experience (at least 3 years) in software engineering, system design, or DevOps, with a focus on observability and monitoring in production environments.
Deep understanding of metrics, logs, and distributed traces, and how they interrelate.
Dynatrace Associate or Professional certification, with proven hands-on experience in administering and using the Dynatrace platform.
In-depth knowledge of Dynatrace Query Language (DQL).
Strong knowledge of cloud environments (Azure or GCP) and containerized architectures (Docker, Kubernetes).
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to perform deep-dive analysis in complex, distributed systems.
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills, capable of translating technical terms for diverse business stakeholders.
A natural curiosity and structured approach to troubleshooting, turning data points into clear narratives.
Solid understanding of ITIL 4 principles.
Skilled in creating reports and dashboards for data-driven decision-making.
Familiarity with JavaScript, Glide API, and ServiceNow automation workflows is a plus.
Proficiency in Infrastructure as Code (Terraform, Dynatrace Monaco, Ansible) and experience with CI/CD concepts (Azure DevOps, GitHub Actions) are highly desirable.
Demonstrated experience in implementing OpenTelemetry and familiarity with defining and tracking SLOs/SLIs and error budgets are also a plus.

If you're ready to make a significant impact and grow your career in a dynamic and supportive environment, we encourage you to apply! We are committed to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace where all voices are heard and valued.

The benefits are good too! 

We offer flexible working in every sense
An exclusive discount card for BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Woolworths, BIG W and other Endeavour Group brands, including our ALH pubs
Monthly meeting-free days 
Your health and wellbeing is your most important asset, and as one of our valued team members, it’s our first priority. You will have a range of free services to help you live well and support your physical, mental and financial wellbeing
Endeavour Group is full of opportunities - use our dedicated learning and development options to grow an idea, yourself, and your career. This is just the start, so dream big.

At Endeavour, we value being a workplace where everyone’s welcome - if you meet a number of the requirements (and not all), we encourage you to apply.

What's in it for you?

We are together creators

With a portfolio that includes Dan Murphy’s, BWS, ALH Hotels, Pinnacle Drinks and more, Endeavour Group is big on sociability. Together we create the moments that bring millions of people together. And together we have more fun, create more opportunities, and score a lot more goals. We’re serious about creating a safe, inclusive and fun place to rock up to where equal opportunity is key, and flexibility is part of how we roll.  

We’re all about creating a more sociable future - for our customers and each other. If this job excites you - and you’re close-enough on the requirements, reach out, we’d love to hear from you.

You can learn more about working with us on LinkedIn or at endeavourgroupcareers.com.au.

Our Talent Team and Hiring Leaders kindly request no unsolicited resumes or approaches from Recruitment Agencies. Endeavour Group is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.

Job Description
Be a part of a passionate team of data enthusiasts
Hybrid and flexible ways of working
Team discounts across Endeavour Group

The Data Engineer - D & AI is a key member of the Group Data Practices team within the D & AI function. This role has line management into the Data Engineering Chapter Lead but receives daily tasks from their delivery squad. 

Endeavour operates an Agile, matrixed environment, with Practices/Chapters providing people management and capabilities, whilst Product squads deliver business missions. Chapter members are embedded in cross-functional delivery squads, bringing their specific skill to that squad. 

Your primary role is to design, build, and deploy technology solutions, as a hands-on technology expert with specialist skills building data products. Depending on the needs of the business, this could be a data service/application and/or product, ML model implementation, Data lake/warehouse data pipelines (cloud GCP, cloud Azure, SQL Server), ETL/ELT, data retention and governance tools implementation, master data management tech implementation, visualisation tools, and analytics tools implementations.

Sitting within cross-functional delivery squads, this role works closely with Business Analysts, Developers, Integration Engineers, Solution Architects, Data Architects, Machine Learning Engineers, Data Scientists, Data Analysts, and domain SMEs to deliver on Tribe missions.

Sound good? Read on.

Here is a taster of what you can expect in this role:

You’re customer-focused and passionate about being part of a tribe of great people and you actively contribute to your workplace community.

With a growth mindset, you orient around doing what’s meaningful, purposeful and delivers value. You’re excited about being part of a data-led transformation at one of Australia’s biggest companies.

You’re curious and empathetic. You have an eye for the bigger picture while also ensuring the details are in order. You deal with complexity by collaborating with colleagues, listening to customers, testing ideas and continuously learning. You take authorship for what you create.

Work with team members and business SMEs to understand the requirements including business problem or opportunity, data requirements, and technology requirements 

Contribute to documentation of requirements and user stories in Jira/Confluence, as required

Build and deploy back-end software services, data applications/services and/or APIs, data pipelines on the data platform

Productionise ML models

Document relevant information required for knowledge sharing across the team and for operational support handover

Knowledge sharing amongst the data engineering chapter and project/squad team members

Collaborate with team and stakeholders to ensure successful delivery

Adhere to technology standards, data governance & privacy policies and security standard, corporate governance policies

Attend/contribute to squad agile ceremonies (e.g. standups, sprint planning etc) , project meetings and deliverables

Build and deploy using devops and infrastructure as code

Provide input into handover to the support team for new builds/enhancements

3rd level support for incidents relating to appropriate productionised data products/services

Comply with the change process and provide inputs, as required, and attend CAB, where required

Qualifications

Now let’s talk about you: 

Software development skills and experience

Back-end development skills, such as APIs

Experience with distributed programming (e.g. Apache Spark)

Cloud data pipeline build, deploy and maintain/support skills

Strong understanding of DBT ( Data Build tool) , Python and PySpark skills, SQL skills

An in-depth understanding of common databases and data structures.

Experience working with big data cloud platforms (Azure, Google Cloud Platform, AWS), Cloud Infrastructure

Experience working in an agile environment

DevOps experience and CI/CD experience

Infrastructure as code experience

Experience with Java and/or C#

Experience with Object-Oriented programming (OOP) , Unit Testing, test driven development (TDD)

Desired: 

Google Cloud Platform experience

Azure Databricks experience

Experience with secure coding practices

Experience working with retail offline (e.g. store sales) and online data sets (e.g. ecommerce)

Experience working with Personally Identifiable Information (PII) data

Experience working with unstructured data

Data science knowledge and/or experience productioning ML models

Retail industry experience

 

The benefits are good too! 

Flexibility first with hybrid work and ways of working that support you, your family and your lifestyle.

Exclusive team discounts across BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Woolworths and more, plus discounts at our ALH Hotels.

Meeting free days, giving you space to focus, grow and recharge.

Health and wellbeing support including free and confidential services including counselling, nutrition and lifestyle advice, financial coaching, family and legal support, to help build confidence resilience and connection

Paid and unpaid leave options including up to 24 months parental leave, personal and carer’s leave, emergency services leave, and gender affirmation leave.

Career growth with learning and development pathways, plus career assist programs to support your goals.

Inclusive culture! We are building a place where everyone belongs, can dream big and leave their mark.

At Endeavour, you will also be connected to our internal inclusion and community networks, including:

EmpowerHER – our women in technology and leadership network, supporting women and allies to grow, connect and lead.

Proud at Endeavour Hub – celebrating and supporting our LGBTQ+ community.

Reconciliation Hub – driving our commitment to First Nations inclusion, recognition and partnership.

Jawun Partner Site – offering unique secondment opportunities to collaborate with First Nations organisations and communities.

Social Crew – bringing our teams together through fun, social and community building events

At Endeavour, we value being a workplace where everyone’s welcome - if you meet a number of the requirements (and not all), we encourage you to apply.

Job Title: Data Engineer (Consultant) - Sydney | Microsoft Fabric / Azure Data Factory
Ad Text:
Make an impact with NTT DATA
Join a company that is pushing the boundaries of what is possible. We are renowned for our technical excellence and leading innovations, and for making a difference to our clients and society. Our workplace embraces diversity and inclusion – it's a place where you can grow, belong and thrive.

Your day at NTT DATA
The Data Engineer (Consultant) is a seasoned subject matter expert, responsible for the transformation of data into a structured format that can be easily analyzed in a query or report.

This role is responsible for developing structured data sets that can be reused or complimented by other data sets and reports.

This role analyzes the data sources and data structure and designs and develops data models to support the analytics requirements of the business which includes management / operational / predictive / data science capabilities.

Key responsibilities:

Creates data models in a structured data format to enable analysis thereof.

Designs and develops scalable extract, transformation and loading (ETL) packages from the business source systems and the development of ETL routines to populate data from sources,

Participates in the transformation of object and data models into appropriate database schemas within design constraints.

Interprets installation standards to meet project needs and produce database components as required.

Creates test scenarios and be responsible for participating in thorough testing and validation to support the accuracy of data transformations.

Accountable for running data migrations across different databases and applications, for example MS Dynamics, Oracle, SAP and other ERP systems.

Works across multiple IT and business teams to define and implement data table structures and data models based on requirements.

Accountable for analysis, and development of ETL and migration documentation.

Collaborates with various stakeholders to evaluate potential data requirements.

Accountable for the definition and management of scoping, requirements, definition, and prioritization activities for small-scale changes and assist with more complex change initiatives.

Collaborates with various stakeholders, contributing to the recommendation of improvements in automated and non-automated components of the data tables, data queries and data models.

To thrive in this role, you need to have:

The skills we require are:
- ETL Design and Development (Microsoft Fabric Data Factory, Databricks, Snowflake)
- Cloud and On-Prem Data Engineering / Warehousing (Azure SQL, Snowflake, Databrick, SSMS/SSIS)
- Programming languages (SQL, Python)
- Version Control (Azure Dev Ops, GIT)
- Data Visualisation (Power BI)
- Data Analysis and Mapping

Seasoned knowledge of the definition and management of scoping requirements, definition and prioritization activities.

Seasoned understanding of database concepts, object and data modelling techniques and design principles and conceptual knowledge of building and maintaining physical and logical data models.

Seasoned expertise in Microsoft Azure Data Factory, SQL Analysis Server.

Minimum 5+ years of hands-on experience with Microsoft Azure Data Factory or Microsoft Fabric is essential for this role.

Seasoned understanding of data architecture landscape between physical and logical data models

Analytical mindset with excellent business acumen skills.

Problem-solving aptitude with the ability to communicate effectively, both written and verbal.

Ability to build effective relationships at all levels within the organization.

Seasoned expert in programing languages (Perl, bash, Shell Scripting, Python, etc.).

Academic qualifications and certifications:

Bachelor's degree or equivalent in computer science, software engineering, information technology, or a related field.

Relevant certifications preferred.

Certified Data Engineer, Certified Professional certification preferred.

Required experience:

Minimum 5 years of experience as Data Engineer (Consultant).

Seasoned experience as a data engineering, data mining within a fast-paced environment.

Proficient in building modern data analytics solutions that delivers insights from large and complex data sets with multi-terabyte scale.

Seasoned experience with architecture and design of secure, highly available and scalable systems.

Seasoned proficiency in automation, scripting and proven examples of successful implementation.

Seasoned proficiency using scripting language (Perl, bash, Shell Scripting, Python, etc.).

Seasoned proficiency in working with SQL, MySQL databases and Microsoft SQL.

Some of our benefits

NTT DATA is a Global and Australian Top Employer, and holds Family Friendly Workplace accreditation. We believe in bringing out the best in you by providing an environment and flexibility that enables you to thrive at work and at home.

As part of the NTT DATA family, here is a small sample of the benefits you will enjoy:

Flexible and hybrid working

Leave options that allow you to contribute to your community, study, or just take time to recharge.

A parental leave policy that supports parents and carers.

Income protection insurance

A comprehensive wellbeing program and associated benefits

Everyone is welcome here

For us, diversity is a strength that is nurtured through an inclusive and fair environment. We're committed to building a diverse workforce, including all and providing everyone with equal opportunities to thrive in their careers.

Workplace type

Hybrid Working

About NTT DATA

NTT DATA is a $30+ billion trusted global innovator of business and technology services. We serve 75% of the Fortune Global 100 and are committed to helping clients innovate, optimize and transform for long-term success. We invest over $3.6 billion each year in R&D to help organizations and society move confidently and sustainably into the digital future. As a Global Top Employer, we have diverse experts in more than 50 countries and a robust partner ecosystem of established and start-up companies. Our services include business and technology consulting, data and artificial intelligence, industry solutions, as well as the development, implementation and management of applications, infrastructure, and connectivity. We are also one of the leading providers of digital and AI infrastructure in the world. NTT DATA is part of NTT Group and headquartered in Tokyo.

Equal Opportunity Employer

NTT DATA is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer with a global culture that embraces diversity. We are committed to providing an environment free of unfair discrimination and harassment. We do not discriminate based on age, race, colour, gender, sexual orientation, religion, nationality, disability, pregnancy, marital status, veteran status, or any other protected category. Join our growing global team and accelerate your career with us.

Australian work rights are required as visa sponsorship will not be considered for this position.

Apply today!

Join a fast-growing tech team developing cutting-edge software for smart manufacturing! Enjoy flexibility, innovation, and competitive rewards.

Our client is a leader in next-generation, smart composite materials and is at the forefront of innovation in the manufacturing sector. As they experience rapid expansion, they are looking for a Power Electronics Engineer to join their dynamic team in Canning Vale, W.A.

Role Overview:

You will need a strong foundation in power electronics engineering, with proven experience in high-power electronics design. Proficiency in DFM/DFA/DFS principles, power electronics simulation tools, structured problem-solving methodologies, experience in fast-paced innovative environments, along with the ability to balance competing priorities, will set you apart.

Requirements
         Investigate and resolve assigned power-related production and field non-conformances (NCR).
         Solve complex power electronics problems using Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA) etc.
         Lead continuous improvement methodologies (NSIS) to optimise power conversion efficiency and thermal management.
         Design and develop advanced low and high-voltage, high-power electronic systems, including inverters, converters, and power control circuits (1kW – 1MW).
         Implement, integrate, test, and debug complex power electronics components and systems.
         Select and specify power semiconductors, magnetic devices, capacitors, and power drive circuits for optimal performance and reliability.
         Utilise simulation tools such as MATLAB/Simulink, LTSpice, Simplorer, and Maxwell for power/frequency/integrity/thermal assessments.
         Design for EMC compliance, ensuring designs meet regulatory standards and certification requirements.
         Prototype and test high-power systems, performing real-time validation and field trials.
         Integrating electrical and electronic commodities within mechanical structures/enclosures.
 
Experience:
         IGBTs, MOSFETs, rectifier circuits, barrier diodes, magnetics, and power conversion devices.
         high-power electronics, inverter/converter design, and power circuit topologies.
         power electronics simulation tools (MATLAB/Simulink, LTSpice, Simplorer, Maxwell).
         DFM/DFA/DFS principles and high-volume manufacturing.
         circuit design software (e.g., ALTIUM) and CAD tools (e.g AutoCAD, SolidWorks etc).
         EMC test equipment and firmware development for 32-bit ARM micro-controllers (with and without RTOS).
         BMS platforms, CANbus communication, and control system integration.
         Power systems related documentation for building and site installation of products.
         power electronics, including rectifier circuits, IGBT, MOSFET, and power conversion devices
         Minimum 3-5 years of experience in an Electronics Industry especially in an R&D and manufacturing environment.
 
Skills:
         Excellent verbal and written communication skills.
         Strong analytical problem-solving and attention to detail.
         Ability to work independently and across multiple disciplines.
         Self-motivated, adaptable, and able to work under pressure.
 
Qualifications:

Degree in Electrical & Electronics Engineering, Power Electronics Engineering or Equivalent.

Job Title: Data and Analytics Engineer - 12-month max. term contract
Ad Text:
Data and Analytics Engineer - 12-month max. term contract
  

Newly created role, leverage analytical and technical skills to implement innovative solutions.
Hybrid work environment, NFP salary packaging, and an opportunity to work with a passionate team and find meaningful work in a for-purpose organisation.
Salary on offer $120,000 + superannuation and access to NFP salary packaging.
  

About the role

Working closely in a small team and reporting into the Head of Data and Insights, you will design and deliver trusted, scalable data models and solutions enabling the organisation to make smarter, faster, and more impactful decisions.
  
You’ll be tasked with building robust integrations, pipelines, automating workflows, and enabling self-service analytics to ensure that high-quality data is accessible, reliable, and aligned to deliver on strategic objectives.
  
Role responsibilities:

Business partner internally to gather data/analytics requirements, and create technical solutions supporting data models, reports, automated workflows, and campaign activities.
Design, build, and maintain scalable ETL pipelines across systems of record (such as CRM) and an Azure Data Warehouse.
Collate data from CRM, finance, and fundraising systems into the Azure Data Lake and Data Warehouse.
Cleanse, normalise, and join datasets to create reusable data models and analytics-ready views of organisational data.
Leverage Azure Data Lake and related tools to support scalable data preparation and storage.
Use Python (including writing automation scripts), SQL, Power Automate, and/or KNIME to streamline workflows, automate recurring extracts and reporting, and reduce manual effort.
Develop APIs and integrations that connect internal systems, and the data warehouse seamlessly.
Create reusable data models and semantic layers that power self-service analytics and consistent reporting. Define key metrics and build dashboards in BI tools to drive better decisions.
Support data retrievals for campaign analytics (target audience lists, response tracking, ROI measurement, etc).
Conduct data quality checks, deduplication processes, metadata management, and security standards to ensure reliable, trusted data.
 
Essential criteria:
  
You’ll thrive when collaborating and designing sophisticated solutions for existing issues and architecture, and be comfortable in a fast-paced and fluid environment.
  
Previous experience in the for-purpose sector will be highly regarded but transferrable industry experience (e.g., Telecommunications, Sales, FMCG, or similar sectors) will also be welcomed.

A Bachelor’s degree in Data Engineering, Data Science, or a related field as well as experience in a hybrid data engineering/analytics engineering role.
Exceptional SQL skills, experience with ETL and data transformation tools (e.g., dbt, Alteryx, custom scripts, or similar).
Proven experience with Python (or another scripting language) for automation.
Experience with at least one Data Warehouse platform (e.g., Azure SQL/Synapse, Redshift, or BigQuery), as well as experience working with CRM platforms and related data models.
Strong experience working with at least one BI tool (Power BI preferred but can also be Tableau or Looker).
Ability to bridge engineering and business systems as well as implement data quality checks, metadata management, or data governance practices.
  
How to Apply

To be considered for this position please apply now with your resume directly through the advertisement. If you have any further questions, please contact Diana Linde at diana@beaumontpeople.com.au.
  
Applications will be assessed as they arrive, please apply immediately if you are interested.

At Beaumont People we believe a diverse workplace is a happy workplace, and we love working with organisations that feel the same way.  We encourage applications from people of all different backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people from CALD backgrounds and people with disabilities.
  
We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, marital or parental status. Should you require a reasonable accommodation to be made for your application to be assessed we would be more than happy to discuss how that can be arranged.

The Role 


We are seeking a Systems Integration Engineer (Level 3) with a background in Mechanical, Electrical, or Mechatronic Engineering and demonstrated expertise in communications systems integration. 


In this role, you will contribute to the delivery of complex, multi-domain engineering projects, providing technical leadership, system integration expertise, and support through all phases of the engineering lifecycle — from requirements analysis to verification and certification. 


Qualifications 


Degree in Engineering (Mechanical, Electrical, Mechatronic, or related discipline). 

Postgraduate qualifications (Master’s or PhD) highly regarded. 


The Job


Interpret user and stakeholder requirements to develop integrated C4I or systems engineering concepts. 

Review mechanical and electrical designs, technical drawings, and specifications to provide subject matter expertise and recommendations. 

Develop and execute elements of the Engineering Management Plan, including Technical Certification Plans, Safety Cases, and supporting documentation. 

Contribute to technical certification processes and engineering change management activities. 

Audit existing configurations and ensure design compliance with applicable standards and specifications. 

Support implementation, rollout, and testing activities to verify conformance with approved designs. 

Conduct requirements analysis, traceability, and management. 

Lead system design, development, and integration activities. 

Execute verification, validation, and certification (V&V) processes. 

Plan and deliver engineering services that meet technical and regulatory requirements. 

Review technical deliverables and provide engineering assessments to support decision-making.


 


About You 


You are a proactive and detail-oriented engineer who thrives in complex, cross-functional environments. You take ownership of technical outcomes, demonstrate sound judgement, and are committed to delivering high-quality engineering solutions. 


You will bring: 


At least 5 years of relevant industry experience delivering engineering services in a systems or integration environment. 

Strong experience in system-level engineering, including requirements definition, hazard analysis, certification, and documentation. 

Proven ability to produce clear and comprehensive design documentation and technical reports. 

Understanding of capability integration principles and frameworks (e.g. operational, technical, and organisational). 

Strong stakeholder engagement and communication skills. 

Ability to manage risk, priorities, and technical delivery within complex project structures. 

Tertiary qualifications or relevant experience in Engineering within Defence or a similarly regulated environment. 

Proven experience delivering complex integration projects. 

Experience working in logistically and technically demanding environments. 

Ability to lead technical integration activities and collaborate across multi-disciplinary teams. 

Current or ability to obtain an NV1 Security Clearance


Next Steps?
